<paragraph blockId="19.[826,1441,1820,1903]" lastBlockId="20.[144,759,196,618]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis box="[826,972,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">Distribution:</emphasis>
According to the present data, this species is restricted to the alpine zone of the Egrigoz Mountain in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1021,1228,1881,1903]" country="Turkey" name="Kutahya" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">Kütahya Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[1264,1345,1881,1903]" name="Turkey" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1361,1425,1881,1903]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[164,243,1159,1178]" captionTargetBox="[167,1440,198,1125]" captionTargetId="figure-293@3.[164,1444,195,1129]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution of the Poecilimon luschani species group (filled circles indicate the specimens used for morphology, song, and DNA studies, see Table 1; open circles indicate the material in the collection of K.G. Heller; taxa names are according to the results of this study)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5287684" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5287684/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[144,251,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">Remarks:</emphasis>
Ünal described this population as a subspecies under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ramme" authorityYear="1933" box="[271,395,228,250]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luschani">
<emphasis box="[271,395,228,250]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">P. luschani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The present data show prominent differences between this population and the other members of the group. An apically widened cercus is shared by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pancic" authorityYear="1883" box="[375,503,320,342]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbelicus">
<emphasis box="[375,503,320,342]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">P. orbelicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Boztepe &amp; Kaya &amp; Çiplak, 2013" authorityName="Boztepe &amp; Kaya &amp; Çiplak" authorityYear="2013" box="[564,663,320,342]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[564,663,320,342]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">P. helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[672,759,321,342]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
However, cercal structure still exhibits some specific aspects. In addition, the male’s subgenital plate with no or indistinct incision is typical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Unal" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Unal" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[590,705,413,434]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egrigozi">
<emphasis box="[590,705,413,434]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">P. egrigozi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pancic" authorityYear="1883" box="[144,272,443,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbelicus">
<emphasis box="[144,272,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">P. orbelicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. More importantly, the molecular phylogeny, based on sequences of two different markers, suggested the species′ close relationships with 
<taxonomicName authority="Boztepe &amp; Kaya &amp; Çiplak, 2013" authorityName="Boztepe &amp; Kaya &amp; Çiplak" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="63">P. helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[191,277,535,556]" pageId="20" pageNumber="63" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and also its independence as a reproductive unit. Therefore, we consider it as an independent species.
</paragraph>
